AnnotationAssertion(obo:IAO_0000115 <http://purl.phyloviz.net/ontology/typon#MLVA> "MLVA stands for Multilocus Variable Number of Tandem Repeats Analysis. This method can be performed by three distinct methodologies: by running the amplified locus in a gel , using a capilary electrophoresis apparatus or sequencing the resulting amplified fragment. The first two infer the number of repeats on each locus indirectly by the fragment size."@en)
